  "title": "IT Manager (Infrastructure, Manufacturing/Semiconductor)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage OSS team and manage all global &amp; local IT Infrastructure activities.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with departments and site managers to meet company goals.</li>\n  <li>Supervise, train, and develop team members.</li>\n  <li>Support budgeting and cost control for IT Infrastructure.</li>\n  <li>Ensure systems run efficiently and are well-maintained.</li>\n  <li>Align local IT priorities with global strategies.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate deployments, system support, and life cycle management.</li>\n  <li>Work with business units to set priorities and optimize resources.</li>\n  <li>Establish best practices and procedures for the team.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Electrical Engineering or Computer Science (MS/BS).</li>\n  <li>At least 6 years of IT Infrastructure experience.</li>\n  <li>Strong in communication, documentation, and teamwork.</li>\n  <li>Solid knowledge of LINUX (SuSE), Windows, and WAN/LAN.</li>\n  <li>Skilled in project and vendor management, with experience in e-commerce projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>______________________________________________________</strong></p>\n<p><strong>HOW TO APPLY :</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Interested candidates, please submit your resume by clicking on “Quick Apply” or contact win@hkmsvs.com for more details.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Please provide following information in the resume for immediate processing</strong></p>\n<p><strong>1) Reasons for leaving current and/or last employment</strong></p>\n<p><strong>2) Last drawn and/or current salary</strong></p>\n<p><strong>3) Expected salary</strong></p>\n<p><strong>4) Date of availability and/or Notice Period</strong></p>\n<p><strong>All applications will be treated in strictest confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Wee Wai Dan</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA License No : 03C5391</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA Reg No : R22109628</strong></p>",
